8-K
1/18/2022
Microsoft Corporation
Acquisition of Activision Blizzard, Inc.

Microsoft Corp. today announced that it has reached a definitive agreement
to acquire Activision Blizzard, Inc. for $68.7 billion in an all-cash
transaction. Under the terms of the agreement, Microsoft will pay $95.00
per share for Activision Blizzard. The transaction is expected to close
in fiscal year 2023 and has been approved by the boards of directors of
both Microsoft and Activision Blizzard. The acquisition is subject to
regulatory review and approval by Activision Blizzard's shareholders.

Bobby Kotick will continue to serve as CEO of Activision Blizzard.
Post-close, Activision Blizzard will report to Microsoft's Gaming division
led by Phil Spencer.

The deal represents Microsoft's largest acquisition to date and positions
the company as the third-largest gaming company by revenue, behind Tencent
and Sony.
